  "instructions": [
    "Combine the onions and garlic in a large bowl and let sit for 10 minutes to allow the onions to release their moisture.",
    "Add the haricot beans, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper to the bowl and mix well.",
    "Cut the butter into small pieces and place on top of the haricot bean mixture.",
    "Place the haricot bean mixture on a large square of parchment paper and fold the paper over to create a packet, sealing the edges with a pinch of water.",
    "Place the papillote on a baking sheet and bake at 400°F for 40 minutes, or until the haricot beans are tender and the paper is golden brown."
